# Public Repository

This repo is PUBLIC. NEVER add secrets, tokens, credentials, personal data, private keys, or internal hostnames. Use runtime env vars for secrets.

# Documentation Sync — BLOCKING

Documentation drift is the #1 maintenance failure in this repo. **Every code change MUST be accompanied by a documentation audit in the same PR/commit series.** Do not consider a task complete until this checklist is satisfied.

## Before you start coding

Read the docs that describe the area you're about to change:

- `README.md` — user-facing
- `CLAUDE.md` and `AGENTS.md` — top-level agent instructions
- `.agents/skills/<topic>/SKILL.md` — the skill closest to your change
- `.agents/rules/*.mdc` — repo-wide rules

If a doc is already wrong about current behavior, fix it as part of your change.

## After every change, audit these surfaces

For each file you touched, run through the matching checklist below. If you can't immediately confirm a doc is still accurate, **read it and verify** — don't assume.

| If you changed... | You MUST check |
|---|---|
| `bin/box` (commands, args, flags, behavior) | `_BOX_COMMANDS` array, case dispatch, `usage()`, both completions heredocs, `README.md` CLI table + workflows, `AGENTS.md` bin/box section, `.agents/skills/box-cli-conventions/SKILL.md` |
| `Containerfile.base` or per-box `Containerfile` | `README.md` package-list / customization sections, `AGENTS.md` Containerfile Conventions, `.agents/skills/containerfile-conventions/SKILL.md`, comments inside the Containerfile (remove stale workaround notes) |
| `box.toml` (any box) or `compile-box-toml.py` | `.agents/skills/box-toml-conventions/SKILL.md`, `AGENTS.md` box.toml conventions section, `.agents/skills/adding-a-box/SKILL.md` template |
| `scripts/init-root.sh`, `init-user.sh`, `shell-init.sh` | `AGENTS.md` Repository Structure (script inventory), `.agents/skills/box-toml-conventions/SKILL.md` "Init script execution contexts" table |
| `.github/workflows/build.yml` | `AGENTS.md` "Image Build Flow" + path-filter notes, `.agents/skills/adding-a-box/SKILL.md` CI section |
| Adding/removing a box | Run the full `.agents/skills/adding-a-box/SKILL.md` checklist |
| Adding a new top-level directory copied into images | Path filters in `build.yml`, `Containerfile.base` COPY, `AGENTS.md` Repository Structure, `.agents/skills/repo-overview/SKILL.md` |

## When you remove a workaround or feature

Greppable cleanup: when a workaround, alias, env var, helper, or feature is removed, search the repo for **every** mention of it (`grep -rn <name>`) and delete the dead references. Stale instructions that point at code that no longer exists are worse than no docs.

## Maintenance contracts

When you add something that must stay in sync with something else (e.g., an array that mirrors a case block, a CI matrix that mirrors a directory list), document the contract in `AGENTS.md` and the relevant skill — not as a comment in source. Future agents will not read source comments to learn invariants.

# Git Commits

- Split commits logically: CI changes, doc/skill updates, and rule changes each get their own commit
- Never push, and never ask whether to push, unless the user explicitly requests it
